@node "Introduction"
      
   @{b}Introduction@{ub}

Welcome to MagnifiCAD. MagnifiCAD is a computer-aided design (CAD) program,
which allows you to produce drawings in 2D with the help of a variety of
tools.

Features:
  
  o Full Intuition GUI with online help for all functions.
  o 10 different drawing tools.
  o Line Styles, Hatching, Colors.
  o Unlimited number of Layers.
  o Unlimited number of entities in each layer.
  o Supports .DXF files for easy exchange of data with other programs.
  o Symbols.
  o Topological levels (element, line, point).

  New in version 1.2:
  
   * @{b}ARexx@{ub}: MagnifiCAD now has an ARexx interface, with these features:
        
        - ARexx Commands for nearly all tools and commands in the program.
        - Script/macro support allowing the user to execute scripts from the Shell or from within MagnifiCAD.
        - 'Record macro' tool to record a sequence of operations.
        - User-definable macro setup.
        - ARexx Command Shell for typing ARexx commands directly while working.

   * @{b}PostScript printing@{ub}: The 'PostScript' printing method is implemented.
        
        - print directly to a PostScript device or to a PostScript file.
        - translate, scale and rotate whole pages.

   * @{b}Redesigned Toolbar@{ub}: The toolbar has been redesigned with new pop-up gadgets.

        - more flexible, logical and clear layout of the tool bar.
        - tool bar adepts to aspect ratios for different screen modes.
        - tools are grouped in lines.
        
   * @{b}Open on own Public screen or Workbench@{ub}: User set public screen.

        - User-set screen font (limited).
        - New 'Screen Settings' requester.
        
   * @{b}Line Drawing Tool@{ub}: This is a new drawing tool for simple lines between 2 points.

   * @{b}Point Drawing Tool@{ub}: This is a new drawing tool for drawing points.

   * @{b}Line Weight@{ub}: Line Weight, allowing different widths of lines, is implemented.

   * @{b}Explode Tool@{ub}: Explode Tool for exploding elements into simpler element types, and symbols into elements.

   * @{b}Move to Front/Back@{ub}: To move elements to front or back of the layer.

   * @{b}Group/Ungroup@{ub}: To group and ungroup elements. Grouped elements can be selected and manipulated as one.

   * @{b}Pick/Snap tools@{ub}: New snap system, using a user set Range to snap to points.

        - User set snap sensitivity (range).
        - Snap Endpoint.
        - Pick Settings requester.
        - Several snap modes can be active at the same time.
        - Pick elements as highlighted or inverted corners.
        
   * @{b}Size Requester@{ub}: To set the work-area size. The size can be altered at any time, and calculated from the elements drawn.
        
   * @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}: Many bugs have been fixed for this version.


@endnode

@node "Requirements"
  
   @{b}System Requirements@{ub}

MagnifiCAD requires:
   
   o An Amiga with WorkBench 3.0 or above, preferrably with a 68020
     processor.
     
   o 1MB free memory.

The size of the projects is limited only by how much free memory you have 
in your Amiga.

MagnifiCAD should run ok on any Amiga with the right WorkBench version.

It will use a math co-processor if one is available, but it is not
required.
@endnode

@node "Installation"

   @{b}Installation@{ub}

An Installer script is included in this directory. Just double-click on
the Install icon from Workbench, and follow the instructions.

This release includes a 68000 version along with the 68020 version.
The Installer script checks your processor and installs the right version
of MagnifiCAD.

@endnode

