@node "Distribution"

   @{b}Distribution@{ub}

All releases of MagnifiCAD will be uploaded as UNREGISTERED versions
on AmiNet, and will also be available from the support pages on
the www.

Registered users will get the latest version of MagnifiCAD when
registering the program and paying the correct amount. This will be
sent by regular post (snail mail) along with the users specific 
keyfile.

Registered users will receive major updates when they are released.
For the registering fee, expect to get the current relase and 2-3
updates.

Minor bugfixes and/or patches may not be sent to all users, but they
will be available at the MagnifiCAD Support Pages.
@endnode


@node "Bugs"

 @{u}@{b}Bugs@{ub}                                                                     @{uu}
 
Known bugs in this version of MagnifiCAD:


@{u}System:@{uu}

 o Doesn't work with MagicMenu (really MM's fault!):
   
   - Reports says that it now works with MagicMenu 2.0 Rev 2.3.
   
 o Locks up when using Picasso screens.
  
  
@{u}Hits/Hangs:@{uu}

 o MagnifiCAD produces Enforcer hits on startup (ouch!).
 
 o Select 'Line/Line' and one of the 3 snaps (PT,MPT,EPT)
   sometimes makes the program hang (at the start).
 
 o If you select the same tool rapidly some times, the program
   hangs. This bug occurs on every object that has a submenu.

 o If the user zooms in many times, the screen update gets distorted.
   (Also happens with hatching). On further zooming, the program hangs!
   
   - This is because of bad clipping routines. I should rewrite the
     clipping routines from scratch myself.

  
@{u}Drawing:@{uu}
 
 o MagnifiCAD doesn't draw a line exactly the line of it.
   (When entering coordinates).
 
 o Panning doesn't work correctly in the middle of a drawing operation.

 o Sliders in project window not working very good.
 
 o Polycurve tends to leave straight lines after drawing.


@{u}Color Requester:@{uu}
 
 o Colors cannot be changed.
 
 o 'Cancel' doesn't work.
 

@{u}Loading/Saving:@{uu}

 o When saving DXF the program seems to lose some parts.
   - Actually, not all the element types are supported in
     the dxf export feature yet.

 o MagnifiCAD cannot handle PC-style files with CR/LF.
 
 
@{u}Printing:@{uu}
 
 o Problems when printing directly to printer, banded gaps,
   no output, etc.
   
   - Make sure that your printer is attached, online and so
     on before you print, because the error handling in the
     printing routines isn't the best(!).

 
@{u}PostScript printing:@{uu}
 
 o When printing directly to a device, no timeout handling
   is implemented yet, so hangs can occur.
 
 o Text is not printed.
 
 o Polycurve only handles 4 points (PS way of handling it).
 
 
 
@endnode


@node "NextVersion"

   @{b}Next Version@{ub}

Something of the things to do for the next version (or future versions) is:

  o Extend line.
  
  o Rulers in Project Window.
  
  o Positioning point.
  
  o Better control with scrollbars.
  
  o More control of TEXT.
  
  o Localized.
  
  o Multiple projects open at the same time.
  
  o More user definable units.
  
  o Font-adaptive GUI (ClassAct?/StormWizard?).
  
  
  ...and maybe it's about time to think of 3D!
  
  
  Comments are welcome!
 

 
@endnode

@node "History"
  
   @{b}History@{ub}
   
  @{u}Version  @{uu} @{u}Date      @{uu} @{u}Description                                    @{uu}


  1.2       01.12.96   Public Release, fixed many bugs, added some
                       small features.
  
  1.2 beta  17.10.96   ARexx Release, with PostScript and new ToolBar.
                       Many new tools and functions.

  1.1       23.01.96   Added better printing, color & depth settings, 
                       scale tool, topological levels, etc.
                       Added keyboard support in requesters.
                       General cleanup and improvement.

  1.0       01.06.95   First version, restricted to 2D drawing.
                       Too many bugs.
         

@endnode

